a=A.y("Research, design, development and evaluation of an open source assistive technology (AT) system to improve the user experience of visually impaired (VI) people. This project is part of my ongoing doctoral studies.",A.v(e9,e9,e9,e9,e9,e9,e9),e9,e9)
a0=s.y
a1=A.w(e9,a0,e9)
a2=A.y("Challenges",s.w,e9,e9)
a0=A.w(e9,a0,e9)
a3=A.y("* When accessing a webpage through a screen reader, much of the visually available information is lost to VI users, or has to be kept in memory at all times (as opposed to just looking at the screen again). \n* Designing technology for users with a completely different experience of the world has to be done carefully to avoid ill-fitted or patronizing devices.\n* Development in the AT field can be slow as it often fails to compete with more financially attractive fields, negatively impacting the cost, availability, support for an AT. ",A.v(e9,e9,e9,e9,e9,e9,e9),e9,e9)
a4=s.y
a5=A.w(e9,a4,e9)
a6=A.y("Approach:",s.w,e9,e9)
a4=A.w(e9,a4,e9)
a7=A.y("* Providing a persistent, interactive and nonvisual (tactile) representation of a webpage to improve the navigation experience of visually impaired users.\n* Participatory design approach, where the research team, clinicians and target users are involved in the conception, construction, improvement and evaluation of the technology to  assess the technology aligns with the needs and realities of the target population.\n* Launching an organization around the project as a platform to connect academics, developers, users and enthusiasts of tactile technology from different fields.\n",A.v(e9,e9,e9,e9,e9,e9,e9),e9,e9)
a8=s.y
a9=A.w(e9,a8,e9)
b0=A.y("Process",s.w,e9,e9)
b1=A.w(e9,a8,e9)
b2=A.y("1. Scientific literature highlights",s.x,e9,e9)
a8=A.w(e9,a8,e9)
b3=A.y("VI:",A.v(e9,e9,e9,e9,e9,B.b6,e9),e9,e9)
b4=A.y("* VI includes the term low vision (visual acuity between 20/40 and 20/400) and blindness (visual acuity worse than 20/400, or a field of view of less than 5 degrees).\n* VI is the most common disability in the world, affecting roughly 253 million people worldwide and 4 million adults in Canada.\n",A.v(e9,e9,e9,e9,e9,e9,e9),e9,e9)
b5=A.y("VI internet navigation:",A.v(e9,e9,e9,e9,e9,B.b6,e9),e9,e9)
b6=A.y("* Audio only screen reader is the AT of choice of about 80% of VI internet users.\n* Getting an overview of the webpage, navigating and learning its structure and skipping to their favorite content are common pain points of the experience of VI internet users. \n* There are no open source tactile stimulation devices available for this kind of development. \n",A.v(e9,e9,e9,e9,e9,e9,e9),e9,e9)
b7=A.y("Design recommendations:",A.v(e9,e9,e9,e9,e9,B.b6,e9),e9,e9)
b8=A.y("* Design around affordances of VI\n* Exploit multimodal interaction and perceptual learning\n* Include latest available tech\n* Adaptable to other populations\n* Unintrusive, discrete and attractive\n* Affordable, upgradable, commercially available, supported. ",A.v(e9,e9,e9,e9,e9,e9,e9),e9,e9)
b9=s.y
c0=A.w(e9,b9,e9)
c1=A.y("2. Initial design",s.x,e9,e9)
b9=A.w(e9,b9,e9)
c2=A.y("Tactile navigator:",A.v(e9,e9,e9,e9,e9,B.b6,e9),e9,e9)
c3=A.y("* A chrome extension extracts the headings of a webpage and displays them on the tactile output of our interface.\n* The interface has four rows of our tactile actuators and interaction buttons. The buttons allow the user to navigate, voice or favorite these headings. Only the previously selected headings are displayed in \u2018favorite\u2019 mode.\n",A.v(e9,e9,e9,e9,e9,e9,e9),e9,e9)
c4=A.y("Tactile actuator:",A.v(e9,e9,e9,e9,e9,B.b6,e9),e9,e9)
c5=A.y("* We developed a simple, affordable and customizable tactile actuator as a base for our device. \nThe actuation mechanism is driven by a Shape Memory Alloy (SMA) wire, and we plan to open source it to enable more people to develop tactile interfaces, to be implemented in assistive technologies, or any other field (gaming, XR, VR neurorehab, etc). \n",A.v(e9,e9,e9,e9,e9,e9,e9),e9,e9)
c6=A.y("Future development:",A.v(e9,e9,e9,e9,e9,B.b6,e9),e9,e9)
c7=A.y("* Anchoring the result of NLP, image description, and other AI algorithms to the tactile representation of the original elements.\n* Displaying other hierarchical information like tables, forms, OOP classes, audiobook index, etc.",A.v(e9,e9,e9,e9,e9,e9,e9),e9,e9)
c8=s.y
c9=A.w(e9,c8,e9)
d0=A.y("3. Co-design",s.x,e9,e9)
c8=A.w(e9,c8,e9)
d1=A.y("* We involved 2 clinicians, and 4 VI clients in a codesign session. \n* We interviewed them about their experiences, perceived barriers and facilitators for internet navigation, and probed for their own ideas for an assistive device. \n* We used Lego bricks to illustrate the idea of a tactile rendering of the headings of a page. \n* We presented a 3dprinted model of the device to illustrate the shape and functions of our original design.  \n* We also attached electronic components to the Lego bricks to make a model of the prototype, so they could intuitively engage in the design process. \n",A.v(e9,e9,e9,e9,e9,e9,e9),e9,e9)
d2=A.y("Two more participants are expected to complete the session, after which, the insights gathered will be used to build an improved design.",A.v(e9,e9,e9,e9,e9,e9,e9),e9,e9)
d3=A.w(e9,s.y,e9)
